<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 4:22PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Meriwether and southeastern Coweta Counties through 445 PM EDT...
At 422 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Moreland, or 9 miles
southeast of Newnan, moving southeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Newnan, Senoia, Grantville, Luthersville, Moreland, Sharpsburg,
Turin, Haralson, Gay, Alvaton, Rocky Mount and Wooster.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
